President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring May 2017 as National Physical Fitness and Sports Month. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of maintaining a healthy and active lifestyle for long-term physical and mental well-being. It highlights the benefits of sports and physical fitness, including disease prevention, teamwork, leadership, and the practice of overcoming adversity. The proclamation also acknowledges the positive impact of sports on mentoring, discipline, and structure for young Americans. President Trump encourages all Americans to prioritize physical activity and sports participation in their lives, and recognizes the individuals who contribute to youth sports and physical activities.